*   Communicate with the Integration team on deploying our nascent containers and take part in the Integration testing. (One person can represent our team in the integration test.).

content:
**Sprint Retrospective:** 

Things that went well: 

*   Dividing teams based on micro services went well as the true spirit of micro services is to organize teams around business capabilities. 
*   Using Scrum of scrum board as the project level Information radiator went well. 

Things that did not go well: 

*   Having a separate Taiga integration team is of no use. 
*   Having a separate Integration team added waste into the process. 
*   Having many people in the group is becoming a challenge. 

Things to do in future sprints: 

*   Fetch your own data. 
*   Do TDD in all your tasks to meet the quality concerns of your project team. 
*   Perform catch up meetings with the Scrum of Scrums on a high level every alternate day for getting precise information.
